CNCP v1 22982
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#10886: v-model.number does not work for radio buttons",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:50.439784+00:00",
  "text": "v-model.number does not work for radio buttons\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.4.25\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- declare radio buttons with values that can be parsed as number\r\n- add a `ref()` and bind the radio buttons with `v-model.number` to it\n\n### What is expected?\n\nThe value of the `ref` should be of type `number`.\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nIt is always of type `string` (tested in Chrome and Firefox.)\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request",
    "scope: v-model"
  ],
